FBIS4-939 "drafr076_c_94024" FBIS-AFR-94-076 Daily Report 20 Apr 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Less Than 500,000 Lacking Identification Documents Less Than 500,000 Lacking Identification Documents MB2004094494 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 0500 GMT 20 Apr 94 MB2004094494 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network English BFN [Text] The Department of Home Affairs says fewer than 500,000 people are still without identity documents or voter's cards. The department says in a statement issued in Pretoria that more than 22 million potential voters are now in possession of the necessary documents. Thousands of identity documents have accumulated at the department's regional and district offices and applicants have been urged to collect them.
